<subSubSection pageId="258" pageNumber="863" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="258.[100,1307,745,1306]" pageId="258" pageNumber="863">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Musser" authorityYear="1991" box="[102,306,1002,1031]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Maxomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="258" pageNumber="863" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="wattsi">Maxomys wattsi</taxonomicName>
is morphologically distinctive compared with all other species of 
<taxonomicName class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Maxomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="258" pageNumber="863" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Maxomys</taxonomicName>
and is probably most closely related to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Jentink" baseAuthorityYear="1879" box="[699,946,1041,1070]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Maxomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="258" pageNumber="863" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="musschenbroekii">M. musschenbroekii</taxonomicName>
; genetic studies are needed to confirm this. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[101,667,1125,1150]" pageId="258" pageNumber="863" type="distribution">
<caption box="[101,667,1125,1150]" inLine="true" pageId="258" pageNumber="863" startId="258.[101,274,1125,1150]" targetBox="[1376,1965,299,715]" targetPageId="258">
